unittitle_ssm: Judith P. Vladeck Papers
abstract_ssm: Judith Pomarlen Vladeck (1923-2007) was a prominent labor and civil rights lawyer, and specialist in cases involving allegations of workplace discrimination against women, winning major cases against Wall Street investment firms, Chase Manhattan Bank, Western Electric and the City University of New York, among other powerful opponents. This collection contains case files for Kyriazi v. Western Electric as well as case files documenting the landmark sex discrimination case of Professor Lilia Melani against the City University of New York.
